uk.gov.gchq.palisade.config.service.request

Class AddConfigRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.gov.gchq.palisade.service.request.Request
      • uk.gov.gchq.palisade.config.service.request.GetConfigRequest
        • uk.gov.gchq.palisade.config.service.request.AddConfigRequest

  • public class AddConfigRequest
extends GetConfigRequest
    A request class that is used by system internal services to add configurations for clients/services into Palisades. This should NOT be used by clients.

    This class has an Optional service field that is used to specify which Service to request the configuration for. If this is left empty, then the Palisade client configuration is set, i.e. the "anonymous" configuration. Note that there may be additional authentication/authorisation constraints placed upon requestees. This means that for example, a client may not be able to set configuration details for a particular service.
